1
00:00:03,867 --> 00:00:06,407
This course doesn't work like most of your other classes.

2
00:00:06,657 --> 00:00:09,127
 There are no exams. No lectures to sit through.

3
00:00:10,177 --> 00:00:13,917
 Instead, you'll work on a real project for a real organization, as part 

4
00:00:13,957 --> 00:00:14,397
of a team.

5
00:00:15,187 --> 00:00:18,697
 That might sound exciting, or it might sound a little intimidating.

6
00:00:19,297 --> 00:00:22,167
 Either way, it's worth understanding why the course is built this 

7
00:00:22,227 --> 00:00:25,337
way. The professional world runs on projects.

8
00:00:25,392 --> 00:00:29,041
 Teams form, figure out a problem together, deliver something, and 

9
00:00:29,122 --> 00:00:30,282
move on to the next one.

10
00:00:31,072 --> 00:00:34,242
 The skills that matter most in that context, things like 

11
00:00:34,262 --> 00:00:38,522
communication, collaboration, critical thinking, those don't 

12
00:00:38,542 --> 00:00:39,902
develop from reading about them.

13
00:00:40,562 --> 00:00:43,772
 They develop from doing them, reflecting on what happened, and 

14
00:00:43,832 --> 00:00:46,586
trying again. That's what experiential learning is.

15
00:00:47,056 --> 00:00:50,056
 You learn by doing real work, not simulated work.

16
00:00:50,386 --> 00:00:53,166
 And because the project is real, the stakes feel different.

17
00:00:53,886 --> 00:00:56,096
 Your employer contact is a real person.

18
00:00:56,416 --> 00:00:58,006
 Your deliverables will be used.

19
00:00:58,396 --> 00:01:00,356
 The feedback you get is professional feedback.

20
00:01:00,856 --> 00:01:04,446
 This week is your on-ramp. No team yet, no project yet.

21
00:01:05,046 --> 00:01:07,376
 Just the foundations you'll need once both arrive.

22
00:01:07,956 --> 00:01:09,046
 Take your time with it.

23
00:01:09,646 --> 00:01:12,246
 Everything you encounter this week will show up again later in the 

24
00:01:12,296 --> 00:01:12,796
course.